	<h2>Alessio Mamo</h2>
	<p>AAlessio Mamo is a Sicilian freelance photographer based in Catania, Italy.
	He received a degree in chemistry in 2004 but prefered to travel rather than to work in a chemical laboratory. In 2007 he graduated in photography from the European Institute of Design in Rome. In 2008 he began his career focusing on contemporary social, political and economic issues. 
	</p>
	<p>His pictures have been published in major international magazines such as Newsweek, The Sunday Times, National Geographic, Geo, Geo voyage, L’Espresso, The Guardian, Le Nouvel Observateur, Focus Historia, Marie Claire, among others. 
	His work is represented by Redux Pictures worldwide.
	</p>
