	<h2>Gözde Türkkan</h2>
	<p>Gözde “mimiko” Türkkan is an artist and photographer living and working based in Istanbul. She studied high school at Lycée Français Pierre Loti in Istanbul and got interested in photography during the year 2000. After receiving her BA degree in 2008 at Istanbul Bilgi University, Türkkan worked as a photography course instructor in the Visual Communication Design Department of the same university. She continued her education at the University of the Arts London, Central Saint Martins, College of Art and Design (London, UK), where she received her MA Fine Art degree in 2010.
	</p>
	<p>Dissecting & Patching (Marseille, 2011), Art HK11 (Hong Kong, 2011), Christie’s auction Visions d’Orient (Paris, 2011), Close Quarters (Istanbul Modern Museum, 2013), Unseen Photo Fair (Amsterdam, 2013) and Landskrona Fotofestival (Sweden, 2014) are among the group shows and art fairs she participated in. Also had 3 solo shows in Istanbul (Looking Back at You 2011, Full Contact 2012, Fight-Flight-Freeze 2013).
