<div class="bio" data-idx="17" style="display: none;">
	<h2>Johan Soussi</h2>
	<p>Johann Soussi was born in 1978 in Paris where he lives and works. He lets us see, without staging and far from platitudes, argentic clichés in black and white which produce a special atmosphere, almost cinematic. Johann Soussi is revealed to the public in 2010 with his first series Aller-Retour preserved today at the National Library of France. His second project, Garde à Vous, is exposed in 2012 at festivals, fairs and galleries in Paris and in several installations outside the Walls. In 2014, he follows the making of the film Les Fusillés and records his new pictures in a work of memory as part of the commemorations of the Great War in partnership with the Mission for the Centenary.
	</p>
</div>
<div class="bio" data-idx="18" style="display: none;">
	<h2>Karine Degiorgis</h2>
	<p>Karine Degiorgios has been working with the photographic medium for some twenty years.
	</p>
	<p>She started showing her work in 1999 in a solo exhibition in Paris, then in various Fairs or Festivals (Salon de Montrouge, Channels OFF Arles Festival in Tokyo, IPEL Festival in Limousin, Salon d’Automne, Transphotographiques in Lille, La Quatrième Image in Paris); in solo exhibitions at Espace 88 Paris, the Château du Gros Buisson Vigneux-sur-Seine, the Paris Briançon 15 Space... and on the websites of Le Bleu du Ciel Gallery, De Visu Gallery, Percept Même Gallery...
